      <abstract>
        <p>Rachel Gabara letter on Richard Eder April 11 review of Links by Nuruddin Farah (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It is misleading to suggest, as does Richard Eder in his review of the novel ''Links'' (April 11), that Nuruddin Farah ''has dispensed with a translator.'' Farah is one of Africa's best-known Anglophone authors. He has published nine novels since 1970, every single one written in an English that is not ''awkward'' but rather poetic as well as precise.</p>
        <p>Rachel Gabara  Princeton, N.J.</p>
      </block>
